The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Yadav reported for tampering
                                                                                                                       7                                      Yadav reported for tampering
            A STAFF REPORTER                      
	Calcutta: George Telegraph bowler Arunlal Yadav has been reported by the umpires for ball tampering during a CAB league match against Dalhousie AC at the Bhowanipore ground on Wednesday.         
	Dalhousie, chasing a target of 219, won by two wickets. Yadav, who took four for 97, was barred from bowling when both on-field umpires Sabyasachi Sarkar and Raju Soni found he was deliberately trying to change the condition of the ball. The ball was changed.         
	Yes, the umpires have submitted a report stating that Yadav has tried to tamper with the ball. The matter will be referred to the tournament committee, a senior official informed.         
	In another move, Barisha Sporting Club has filed a complaint against umpires Biplab Basu and Kanishka Roy Chowdhury on grounds of poor umpiring standard. The CAB tournament committee also referred West Bengal Police captain Arindam Dass name to the cricket committee for punishment for poor conduct.                                                                                                                     
